#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:8
#, kde-format
msgid "Attacks"
msgstr "Attacks"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:9
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:13
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"A list of times in seconds for each channel over which the instantaneous "
"level of the input signal is averaged to determine its volume. Attacks "
"refers to increase of volume and decays refers to decrease of volume. For "
"most situations, the attack time (response to the audio getting louder) "
"should be shorter than the decay time, because the human ear is more "
"sensitive to sudden loud audio than sudden soft audio. A typical value for "
"attack is 0.3 seconds and a typical value for decay is 0.8 seconds. If "
"specified number of attacks and decays is lower than number of channels, the "
"last set attack/decay will be used for all remaining channels."
msgstr ""
"ລາຍການເວລາເປັນວິນາທີສຳລັບແຕ່ລະຊ່ອງທີ່ລະດັບທັນທີຂອງສັນຍານຂາເຂົ້າຖືກສະເລ່ຍເພື່ອກຳນົດລະດັບສຽງ. "
"Attacks ໝາຍເຖິງການເພີ່ມຂຶ້ນຂອງລະດັບສຽງ ແລະ decays ໝາຍເຖິງການຫຼຸດລົງຂອງລະດັບສຽງ. "
"ສຳລັບສະຖານະການສ່ວນໃຫຍ່, ເວລາ attack (ການຕອບສະໜອງຕໍ່ສຽງທີ່ດັງຂຶ້ນ) ຄວນຈະສັ້ນກວ່າເວລາ "
"decay, ເພາະວ່າຫູຂອງມະນຸດມີຄວາມອ່ອນໄຫວຕໍ່ສຽງດັງກະທັນຫັນຫຼາຍກວ່າສຽງຄ່ອຍກະທັນຫັນ. ຄ່າປົກກະຕິສຳລັບ "
"attack ແມ່ນ 0.3 ວິນາທີ ແລະ ຄ່າປົກກະຕິສຳລັບ decay ແມ່ນ 0.8 ວິນາທີ. ຖ້າຈຳນວນ attacks ແລະ "
"decays ທີ່ລະບຸໜ້ອຍກວ່າຈຳນວນຊ່ອງ, attack/decay ຊຸດສຸດທ້າຍຈະຖືກໃຊ້ສຳລັບຊ່ອງທີ່ເຫຼືອທັງໝົດ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:12
#, kde-format
msgid "Decays"
msgstr "Decays"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:16
#, kde-format
msgid "Soft-Knee"
msgstr "Soft-Knee"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:17
#, kde-format
msgid "Set the curve radius in dB for all joints."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງລັດສະໝີເສັ້ນໂຄ້ງເປັນ dB ສຳລັບທຸກຂໍ້ຕໍ່."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:21
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set the additional gain in dB to be applied at all points on the transfer "
"function. This allows for easy adjustment of the overall gain."
msgstr ""
"ຕັ້ງຄ່າອັດຕາຂະຫຍາຍເພີ່ມເຕີມເປັນ dB ທີ່ຈະໃຊ້ກັບທຸກຈຸດໃນ transfer function. "
"ສິ່ງນີ້ຊ່ວຍໃຫ້ປັບອັດຕາຂະຫຍາຍໂດຍລວມໄດ້ງ່າຍ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:24
#, kde-format
msgid "Initial volume"
msgstr "ລະດັບສຽງເລີ່ມຕົ້ນ"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:25
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set an initial volume, in dB, to be assumed for each channel when filtering "
"starts. This permits the user to supply a nominal level initially, so that, "
"for example, a very large gain is not applied to initial signal levels "
"before the companding has begun to operate. A typical value for audio which "
"is initially quiet is -90 dB."
msgstr ""
"ຕັ້ງຄ່າລະດັບສຽງເລີ່ມຕົ້ນ, ເປັນ dB, ທີ່ຈະສົມມຸດສຳລັບແຕ່ລະຊ່ອງເມື່ອການຟິວເຕີເລີ່ມຕົ້ນ. "
"ສິ່ງນີ້ອະນຸຍາດໃຫ້ຜູ້ໃຊ້ລະບຸລະດັບ nominal ໃນເບື້ອງຕົ້ນ, ຕົວຢ່າງ, "
"ເພື່ອບໍ່ໃຫ້ໃຊ້ອັດຕາຂະຫຍາຍທີ່ໃຫຍ່ຫຼາຍກັບລະດັບສັນຍານເລີ່ມຕົ້ນກ່ອນທີ່ companding ຈະເລີ່ມເຮັດວຽກ. "
"ຄ່າປົກກະຕິສຳລັບສຽງທີ່ງຽບໃນຕອນຕົ້ນແມ່ນ -90 dB."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:4
#, kde-format
msgid "Compensation Delay"
msgstr "Compensation Delay"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:8
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Compensation Delay Line is a metric based delay to compensate differing "
"positions of microphones or speakers.\n"
"For example, you have recorded guitar with two microphones placed in "
"different locations. Because the front of sound wave has fixed speed in "
"normal conditions, the phasing of microphones can vary and depends on their "
"location and interposition. The best sound mix can be achieved when these "
"microphones are in phase (synchronized). Note that a distance of ~30 cm "
"between microphones makes one microphone capture the signal in antiphase to "
"the other microphone. That makes the final mix sound moody. This filter "
"helps to solve phasing problems by adding different delays to each "
"microphone track and make them synchronized.\n"
"\n"
"The best result can be reached when you take one track as base and "
"synchronize other tracks one by one with it. Remember that synchronization/"
"delay tolerance depends on sample rate, too. Higher sample rates will give "
"more tolerance. "
msgstr ""
"Compensation Delay Line ແມ່ນ delay ທີ່ອີງໃສ່ metric "
"ເພື່ອຊົດເຊີຍຕຳແໜ່ງທີ່ແຕກຕ່າງກັນຂອງໄມໂຄຣໂຟນ ຫຼື ລຳໂພງ.\n"
"ຕົວຢ່າງ, ເຈົ້າໄດ້ບັນທຶກສຽງກີຕ້າດ້ວຍສອງໄມໂຄຣໂຟນທີ່ວາງໄວ້ໃນຕຳແໜ່ງທີ່ແຕກຕ່າງກັນ. "
"ເນື່ອງຈາກໜ້າຄື້ນສຽງມີຄວາມໄວຄົງທີ່ໃນສະພາວະປົກກະຕິ, phasing ຂອງໄມໂຄຣໂຟນອາດຈະແຕກຕ່າງກັນ ແລະ "
"ຂຶ້ນກັບຕຳແໜ່ງ ແລະ ການວາງຊ້ອນກັນ. ການປະສົມສຽງທີ່ດີທີ່ສຸດສາມາດບັນລຸໄດ້ເມື່ອໄມໂຄຣໂຟນເຫຼົ່ານີ້ຢູ່ໃນເຟສ "
"(synchronized). ສັງເກດວ່າໄລຍະຫ່າງ ~30 ຊມ ລະຫວ່າງໄມໂຄຣໂຟນເຮັດໃຫ້ໄມໂຄຣໂຟນໜຶ່ງຈັບສັນຍານໃນ "
"antiphase ກັບອີກໄມໂຄຣໂຟນໜຶ່ງ. ນັ້ນເຮັດໃຫ້ສຽງປະສົມສຸດທ້າຍຟັງແລ້ວບໍ່ດີ. ຟິວເຕີນີ້ຊ່ວຍແກ້ໄຂບັນຫາ "
"phasing ໂດຍການເພີ່ມ delay ທີ່ແຕກຕ່າງກັນໃຫ້ກັບແຕ່ລະແທຣັກໄມໂຄຣໂຟນ ແລະ ເຮັດໃຫ້ພວກມັນ "
"synchronized.\n"
"\n"
"ຜົນລົບບທີ່ດີທີ່ສຸດສາມາດບັນລຸໄດ້ເມື່ອເຈົ້າເອົາແທຣັກໜຶ່ງເປັນຖານ ແລະ synchronize ແທຣັກອື່ນເທື່ອລະອັນກັບມັນ. "
"ຈື່ໄວ້ວ່າຄວາມທົນທານຂອງ synchronization/delay ຂຶ້ນກັບ sample rate ເຊັ່ນກັນ. Sample rate "
"ທີ່ສູງກວ່າຈະໃຫ້ຄວາມທົນທານຫຼາຍກວ່າ. "

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:11
#, kde-format
msgid "Millimeter distance"
msgstr "ໄລຍະຫ່າງມິນລິແມັດ"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:12
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set millimeters distance. This is compensation distance for fine tuning."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງໄລຍະຫ່າງເປັນມິນລິແມັດ. ນີ້ແມ່ນໄລຍະຫ່າງຊົດເຊີຍສຳລັບການປັບລະອຽດ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:15
#, kde-format
msgid "Centimeter distance"
msgstr "ໄລຍະຫ່າງຊັງຕີແມັດ"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:16
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set cm distance. This is compensation distance for tightening distance setup."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງໄລຍະຫ່າງເປັນຊມ. ນີ້ແມ່ນໄລຍະຫ່າງຊົດເຊີຍສຳລັບການຕັ້ງຄ່າໄລຍະຫ່າງໃຫ້ແໜ້ນຂຶ້ນ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:19
#, kde-format
msgid "Meter distance"
msgstr "ໄລຍະຫ່າງແມັດ"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:20
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set meters distance. This is compensation distance for hard distance setup."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງໄລຍະຫ່າງເປັນແມັດ. ນີ້ແມ່ນໄລຍະຫ່າງຊົດເຊີຍສຳລັບການຕັ້ງຄ່າໄລຍະຫ່າງແບບແຂງ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:23
#, kde-format
msgid "Dry amount"
msgstr "ປະລິມານ Dry"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:24
#, kde-format
msgid "Set dry amount. Amount of unprocessed (dry) signal."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງປະລິມານ dry. ປະລິມານຂອງສັນຍານທີ່ບໍ່ໄດ້ປະມວນຜົນ (dry)."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:27
#, kde-format
msgid "Wet amount"
msgstr "ປະລິມານ Wet"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:28
#, kde-format
msgid "Set wet amount. Amount of processed (wet) signal."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງປະລິມານ wet. ປະລິມານຂອງສັນຍານທີ່ປະມວນຜົນແລ້ວ (wet)."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:32
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set temperature in degrees Celsius. This is the temperature of the "
"environment."
msgstr "ຕັ້ງອຸນຫະພູມເປັນອົງສາເຊນຊຽດ. ນີ້ແມ່ນອຸນຫະພູມຂອງສະພາບແວດລ້ອມ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crossfeed.xml:4
#, kde-format
msgid "Crossfeed"
msgstr "Crossfeed"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crossfeed.xml:7
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Apply headphone crossfeed filter.\n"
"Crossfeed is the process of blending the left and right channels of stereo "
"audio recording. It is mainly used to reduce extreme stereo separation of "
"low frequencies.\n"
"The intent is to produce more speaker like sound to the listener."
msgstr ""
"ໃຊ້ຟິວເຕີ headphone crossfeed.\n"
"Crossfeed ແມ່ນຂະບວນການປະສົມຊ່ອງຊ້າຍ ແລະ ຂວາຂອງການບັນທຶກສຽງ stereo. "
"ມັນຖືກໃຊ້ສ່ວນໃຫຍ່ເພື່ອຫຼຸດການແຍກ stereo ທີ່ຮຸນແຮງຂອງຄວາມຖີ່ຕໍ່າ.\n"
"ຈຸດປະສົງແມ່ນເພື່ອຜະລິດສຽງທີ່ຄ້າຍຄືລຳໂພງຫຼາຍຂຶ້ນໃຫ້ກັບຜູ້ຟັງ."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crossfeed.xml:13
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set strength of crossfeed.\n"
"Default is 0.2. Allowed range is from 0 to 1. This sets gain of low shelf "
"filter for side part of stereo image.\n"
"Default is -6dB. Max allowed is -30db when strength is set to 1."
msgstr ""
"ຕັ້ງຄວາມແຮງຂອງ crossfeed.\n"
"ຄ່າເລີ່ມຕົ້ນແມ່ນ 0.2. ຊ່ວງທີ່ອະນຸຍາດແມ່ນຈາກ 0 ຫາ 1. ນີ້ຕັ້ງອັດຕາຂະຫຍາຍຂອງ low shelf filter "
"ສຳລັບສ່ວນຂ້າງຂອງພາບ stereo.\n"
"ຄ່າເລີ່ມຕົ້ນແມ່ນ -6dB. ສູງສຸດທີ່ອະນຸຍາດແມ່ນ -30db ເມື່ອຄວາມແຮງຖືກຕັ້ງເປັນ 1."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crossfeed.xml:19
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set soundstage wideness.\n"
"Default is 0.5. Allowed range is from 0 to 1. This sets cut off frequency of "
"low shelf filter.\n"
"Default is cut off near 1550 Hz. With range set to 1 cut off frequency is "
"set to 2100 Hz. "
msgstr ""
"ຕັ້ງຄວາມກວ້າງຂອງ soundstage.\n"
"ຄ່າເລີ່ມຕົ້ນແມ່ນ 0.5. ຊ່ວງທີ່ອະນຸຍາດແມ່ນຈາກ 0 ຫາ 1. ນີ້ຕັ້ງຄວາມຖີ່ cut off ຂອງ low shelf "
"filter.\n"
"ຄ່າເລີ່ມຕົ້ນແມ່ນ cut off ໃກ້ 1550 Hz. ເມື່ອ range ຖືກຕັ້ງເປັນ 1 ຄວາມຖີ່ cut off ຈະຖືກຕັ້ງເປັນ "
"2100 Hz. "

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crystalizer.xml:4
#, kde-format
msgid "Crystalizer"
msgstr "Crystalizer"

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crystalizer.xml:6
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Simple algorithm for audio noise sharpening.\n"
"This filter linearly increases differences between each audio sample."
msgstr ""
"ອັນກໍຣິທຶມງ່າຍໆສຳລັບ audio noise sharpening.\n"
"ຟິວເຕີນີ້ເພີ່ມຄວາມແຕກຕ່າງລະຫວ່າງແຕ່ລະຕົວຢ່າງສຽງແບບ linear."

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crystalizer.xml:12
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Sets the intensity of effect (default: 2.0).\n"
"Must be in range between -10.0 to 0 (unchanged sound) to 10.0 (maximum "
"effect).\n"
"To inverse filtering use negative value. "
msgstr ""
"ຕັ້ງຄວາມເຂັ້ມຂອງເອັບເຟັກ (ຄ່າເລີ່ມຕົ້ນ: 2.0).\n"
"ຕ້ອງຢູ່ໃນຊ່ວງລະຫວ່າງ -10.0 ຫາ 0 (ສຽງບໍ່ປ່ຽນແປງ) ຫາ 10.0 (ເອັບເຟັກສູງສຸດ).\n"
"ເພື່ອ inverse filtering ໃຫ້ໃຊ້ຄ່າລົບ. "

#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_crystalizer.xml:15
